The paper discusses the design and optimization of an implementation of hierarchical associative arrays for analyzing network data, which falls under the categories of database systems (cs.DB) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the performance of the implementation in terms of network infrastructure (cs.NI) and machine learning (cs.LG) applications. Finally, the paper discusses the use of mathematical guarantees such as linearity, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
